                    <p>If possible, please arrive for our Welcome Drinks Gathering at 7:30 on Thursday night.</p>
                     
                    <p>Northstar Resort is 45 minutes from Reno International Airport and a 3-4 hour drive from San Francisco. **Winter driving in this area is intense! Either 4 wheel drive or tire chains are required by law. Please don’t take this lightly!</p>

                    <p>The wedding itself will be at the Ritz Carlton Hotel. Lodging and other gatherings will be in Northstar Village, which is connected to the Ritz by gondola.</p>
                     
                    <h2>Do I Have to Drive?</h2>
                    <p>Nope. As long as you are staying in Northstar <span class="italics">Village</span>, you can get everywhere on foot or by gondola. Outside the village, free shuttles run within the resort from 8 am to 10 pm. Call one at 530.562.2257. Put it in your phone right now!</p>
                     
                    <h2>How Do I Get To And From the Airport?</h2>
                    <p>Taxis run between Reno Airport and Northstar 24 Hours. One way service is roughly $90 for up to 4 people, $10 each additional person.  Try Lakeshore Taxi at 530.544.3600 or Elite Tahoe Taxi at 530.580.8294. Advanced reservations are recommended, especially for groups.</p>

                    <p>A more affordable option, especially for singles, is North Lake Tahoe Express Shuttle. It’s a scheduled shuttle for $45 one way (or less, if you have more people). Advance reservations are required. Call 866.216.5222. Here are the times:</p>
